<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3806300>
    dc:description "Fig. 29. Siriella vincenti W.M. Tattersall, 1927, syntype, ♀, length 7.5 mm, Gulf of St. Vincent, South Australia. A. Anterodorsal margin of carapace and subrostral process. B. Dorsal part of carapace, lateral view. C. Telson. D. Apical part of telson, dorsal view. E. Uropodal exopod, ventral view. F. Uropodal endopod, ventral view. Scale bars: A–C, E–F = 0.5 mm; D = 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3806300/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3806304>
    dc:description "Fig. 30. Siriella vincenti W.M. Tattersall, 1927, syntypes, Gulf of St. Vincent, South Australia, Australia. A. Antenna 1 peduncle, dorsal view. B. Antenna 1 peduncle, dorsal view. C. Antenna 2 peduncle and antennal scale, ventral view. D. Mandibular palp, medial view. E. Labrum. F. Distal part of maxilliped 1 endopod, posterior view. A, C–F = ♀; B = ♂, length 7.5 mm. Scale bars: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–F = 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3806304/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3806308>
    dc:description "Fig. 31. Siriella vincenti W.M. Tattersall, 1927, syntypes, Gulf of St. Vincent, South Australia, Australia. A. Maxilliped 2 endopod, posterior view. B. Distal part of maxilliped 2 endopod, posterior view. C. Pereopod 1 endopod, posterior view. D. Pleopod 4, posterior view. A–C = ♀, length 7.5 mm; D = ♂, length 7.5 mm. Scale bars: A, C–D = 0.5 mm; B = 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3806308/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

